  "ciliary_role": "Also known as NPHP5. Required for extension of an axoneme after docking of the basal body to the cell membrane. Absence leads to mislocalization of BBS2, BBS5 and destroys BBSome integrity (27328943). Interacts with CEP290 and is required for early cilia assembly, migration and/or anchoring of centrosomes to the cell cortex (23446637). NPHP5-binding to the BBSome is crucial for BBSome integrity and ciliary trafficking (25552655).",
